132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1931
H.P. 1292 House of Representatives, May 6, 2025
An Act to Annually Reimburse the Town of Charleston for 43
Percent of Property Tax Revenue Lost Due to the Mountain View
Correctional Facility's Tax-exempt Status
Reference to the Committee on Taxation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative FOSTER of Dexter.
Cosponsored by Senator GUERIN of Penobscot and
Representative: PERKINS of Dover-Foxcroft.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §662 is enacted to read:
3 §662. Reimbursement to Town of Charleston
4 The Treasurer of State shall annually reimburse the Town of Charleston an amount
5 equal to 43% of the property tax revenue loss suffered by the town during the previous
6 calendar year as a result of the exemption from property tax afforded to the Mountain View
7 Correctional Facility pursuant to section 651.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill requires the Treasurer of State to annually reimburse the Town of Charleston
1100 for 43% of the property tax revenue loss suffered by the town in the previous calendar year
1111 as a result of the tax exemption that applies to the Mountain View Correctional Facility.
